    "ws_gen_syllable_min": "Teeb the minimum syllable suav for tau tsim lo lus. Range: 1 syllable (cat, dog) to 4+ syllables (hippopotamus). Syllable suav correlates with decoding kev nyuaj. 1-syllable lo lus: CVC patterns, beginning readers, phoneme segmentation focus. 2-syllable lo lus: introduce syllable kev faib, compound lo lus, affixes. 3+ syllable lo lus: qib siab decoding, morphology awareness. Siv with Max Syllables to tsim tshwj xeeb ranges: teeb both to 2 for two-syllable xyaum only. cov lus qhia: kev nce qib from fewer syllables to ntau as tub ntxhais kawm build kev txawj. Multisyllabic lo lus cov lus qhia is critical for upper elementary fluency development.",
