    "ws_gen_src_glossary": "Pull cov lus from your qhib phau ntawv qhia lus into phonics xyaum. phau ntawv qhia lus lo lus provide: curriculum-aligned cov lus, familiar context for tub ntxhais kawm, and reinforcement of zaj lus qhia cov ntsiab. Only qhib phau ntawv qhia lus lo lus are suav nrog. Combine with other lo lus sources for variety. phau ntawv qhia lus lo lus txais same phonetic processing: IPA transcription, syllable breakdown, and pronunciation suab. Great for: unit review, cov lus reinforcement, and connecting reading to phonics. cov lus qhia: Build phau ntawv qhia lus thawj, then siv qhov no kev xaiv for integrated cov lus-phonics cov lus qhia.",
    "ws_gen_src_family": "Focus xyaum on rhyming lo lus patterns. lo lus families (rimes) sib koom: ending sounds, spelling patterns, and decoding tswv yim. piv txwv: -at family (cat, hat, bat), -ight family (light, night, right). Learning lo lus families: builds pattern recognition, accelerates decoding of tshiab lo lus, and develops phonemic awareness. Xaiv a family from the dropdown after enabling qhov no kev xaiv. AI expands the family with additional valid lo lus. Perfect for: beginning readers, pattern-based cov lus qhia, and rhyme awareness. cov lus qhia: Teach one lo lus family thoroughly before introducing another.",
