    "export_pdf": "Xa tawm your current zaj lus qhia pack or tau xaiv kev pab cuam as a luam tawm-ready PDF. PDF preserves: all tau tsim cov ntsiab, embedded duab and duab piav qhia, phau ntawv qhia lus lub rooj, kev sim lo lus teb keys (if pom tau), and proper page break logic. Best for: printing physical handouts, sending home with tub ntxhais kawm, archiving the zaj lus qhia for tom ntej year, niam txiv communication, and substitute xib fwb folders. PDF generation takes 5-20 seconds depending on duab suav. cov ntaub ntawv downloads to your browser's default rub los folder with a date-stamped filename. cov lus qhia: if you plan to kho the cov ntawv further (e.g., ntxiv district-tshwj xeeb branding), xa tawm to lo lus instead — PDF is best for final, frozen materials.",
    "read_this_page_toggle": "Qhib the Nyeem Qhov no Page phab ntsa — a screen-reader-hom overlay qhov ntawd lets tub ntxhais kawm (or xib fwb checking accessibility) hear the current page aloud with keyboard-driven navigation. cov yam ntxwv: Nyeem All pob nias qhov ntawd reads the page in semantic order (headings → nqe lus → list yam), Nres control, Keyboard Focus Narration hloov (Tab through controls and hear what each does), and high-contrast theming for low-vision users. Works alongside your OS screen reader (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver) — does not conflict, just provides an in-app kev xaiv for users who don't have a screen reader installed. cov lus qhia: the Keyboard Focus Narration hom is especially useful for xib fwb verifying their tau tsim materials are screen-reader-friendly before sharing with a tub ntxhais kawm who siv AT.",
    "immersive_focus_mode": "Full-screen distraction-free reading hom. Strips away the AlloFlow UI and presents one chunk of cov ntawv at a time on a calm background — designed for tub ntxhais kawm with ADHD, sensory sensitivities, or anyone who needs to lower kev pom noise to focus. Controls: tap to advance, configurable lo lus-per-chunk, suab playback with adjustable ceev, and a 'chunk mood' kev teeb tsa qhov ntawd tints the background based on suab. Exits with Escape key or the kaw pob nias. cov lus qhia: pair Focus hom with reduced-kev txav CSS for tub ntxhais kawm who report cybersickness from animations — the combination yields the calmest reading environment AlloFlow offers.",
    "immersive_chunk_mood": "Tints the chunk background based on detected emotional suab. AI infers the mood from the chunk's cov ntsiab (e.g., suspenseful passage → cool blue-purple, hopeful passage → warm amber, neutral expository → soft slate) and applies a subtle background gradient. Designed to give kev pom-processing tub ntxhais kawm an additional cue about emotional register beyond the lo lus themselves — particularly helpful for autistic readers building literal-to-affective reading kev txawj. Off by default to keep the reading surface neutral; turn on when teaching suab, mood, or characterization. cov lus qhia: discuss with tub ntxhais kawm BEFORE turning it on — some prefer the neutral surface; for others, the xim cue is the difference between catching the mood shift or missing it.",
    "immersive_chunk_read_along": "Synchronized highlighting qhov ntawd follows the TTS suab through the cov ntawv — the current lo lus is highlighted as it is nyeem aloud. Implements the tus qauv 'karaoke' bouncing-ball pattern proven in dyslexia research (Kintsch & van Dijk; Carnine et al.) to improve lo lus-to-sound mapping and tracking. Highlighting xim is customizable (yellow underline by default for high contrast on light backgrounds, switches to amber on dark ntsiab lus). Works at any suab ceev. cov lus qhia: for emerging readers, pib at 75% ceev with nyeem-along on; ceev up as fluency improves. For tub ntxhais kawm with ocular tracking difficulties, the highlight gives the eye a kev pom anchor qhov ntawd reduces kab-loss.",
    "immersive_font_family": "Pick the font for the immersive reading surface. Lexend: research-backed for fluency improvement, especially for readers with low vision or processing variability. OpenDyslexic: weighted-bottom letters reduce confusion between b/d/p/q for dyslexic readers (preference varies — let tub ntxhais kawm xaiv). Atkinson: designed by the Braille Institute for low-vision accessibility, also zoo for general readability. Georgia: classic serif, comfortable for ntev-form reading. Inter: clean sans-serif, modern default. Comic Sans: yog really — research (de Leeuw 2010) found dyslexic readers preferred it; do not strip it for aesthetic reasons. cov lus qhia: don't pick FOR the tub ntxhais kawm — qhia them the picker and let them kev sim over a week; reading preference is highly individual.",
    "immersive_karaoke_overlay": "Cinematic karaoke-reader overlay: cov ntawv scrolls vertically through a stylized 'stage' display while the TTS suab reads, with synchronized kab highlighting. Designed for engaging reluctant readers and for shared-screen nyeem-alouds (project on the smartboard and the whole chav kawm follows along). Configurable palette (Golden / Aqua / Paper), playback ceev, and auto-advance kev coj noj coj ua. Especially effective for poetry, song lyrics, dialogue, and any cov ntawv where rhythm and pacing matter to comprehension. cov lus qhia: siv Karaoke hom for the thawj nyeem-through of a poem, then hloov to Focus hom for kaw-reading and annotation — different hom serve different stages of the reading workshop.",
    "immersive_perspective_crawl": "Star Wars-hom cinematic crawl overlay where cov ntawv scrolls upward at an kaum on a starfield background. Pure novelty engagement for reluctant readers who associate cov ntawv with effort — pairs the cov ntsiab with a kev pom trope they already love. Best for: luv passages, important quotes, dramatic excerpts, and chav kawm-opening hooks. Not recommended for sustained reading (the kaum and kev txav are fatiguing past ~5 minutes) or for tub ntxhais kawm with vestibular sensitivity (kev txav-induced discomfort). Configurable scroll ceev and palette. cov lus qhia: siv sparingly and strategically — overused, the novelty wears off. Best deployed as the OPENING hook of a zaj lus qhia, not the main reading activity.",
    "concept_sort_image_mode": "Whether muab cais daim npav suav nrog AI-tau tsim duab. Auto (default): duab appear only on daim npav with luv cov ntawv labels (≤4 lo lus) where they meaningfully aid recognition; ntev-cov ntawv daim npav stay cov ntawv-only since the duab would compete with the lo lus. Always: every daim npav gets an duab — best for K-2 tub ntxhais kawm still building lo lus-duab connections, or for ELL classrooms where the duab is the bridge to the English label. Never: cov ntawv-only daim npav (fastest generation, smallest xa tawm PDF, best for older tub ntxhais kawm who don't need the kev pom scaffold). duab generation adds ~3-5 seconds per daim npav. cov lus qhia: Always-hom for primary, Auto for late-elementary and beyond, Never for AP/honors chav kawm.",
