    "timeline_mode_info": "Xaiv the timeline hom qhov ntawd matches your cov ntsiab. Chronological: classic time-ordered events (historical events, biographies, dab neeg plots). Process: sequential cov theem with no calendar dates (photosynthesis stages, water cycle, scientific method, writing process). Narrative Arc: dab neeg structure (Exposition → Rising Action → Climax → Falling Action → Resolution) — best for literature analysis. Each hom adjusts AI prompts: Chronological extracts dates and durations; Process extracts cov theem tus lej and dependencies; Narrative Arc extracts dab neeg stages and emotional peaks. hom also affects the kev ua si playback — chronological qhia years on daim npav, Process qhia cov theem tus lej, Narrative Arc qhia arc-shaped layout. cov lus qhia: do not lub zog Chronological onto Process cov ntsiab; AI will invent fake dates rather than admit there are none.",
    "timeline_image_style": "tsis yog yuav tsum hom cov lus qhia applied to every duab tau tsim for timeline events, keeping the kev pom aesthetic consistent across the whole sequence. piv txwv: 'period illustration', 'photorealistic historical photo', 'watercolor', 'flat vector', 'kab drawing in scientific journal hom'. Empty = default mixed hom. Consistent imagery reduces cognitive nqa los — tub ntxhais kawm focus on the sequence, not the changing art hom. For historical timelines, 'period illustration' or 'sepia photograph' tsim immersion; for science processes, 'scientific duab piav qhia' fits; for narrative arcs, 'phau ntawv dab neeg illustration' works well. Persists with the timeline so any duab refines stay on-brand. cov lus qhia: match hom to cov ntsiab domain — modern flat vectors break the spell on a Civil War timeline.",
    "timeline_hint_btn": "Reveal a cov lus qhia for the currently qhib timeline daim npav without giving away the lo lus teb. The cov lus qhia AI surfaces ONE piece of contextual cov ncauj lus qhov ntawd nudges the tub ntxhais kawm toward the correct chronological position (e.g., 'Qhov no event happened during the same decade as X' or 'Qhov no was a cause of the event you've already placed'). Costs no XP but slightly reduces the final nqi zog to discourage cov lus qhia-spam. cov lus qhia kev nyuaj scales: thawj cov lus qhia is vague, repeated cov lus qhia get ntau tshwj xeeb. cov lus qhia: encourage tub ntxhais kawm to siv cov lus qhia as a productive struggle pib dua rather than as a shortcut — talk about what the cov lus qhia revealed and why before placing the daim npav.",
    "timeline_reveal_btn": "Qhia the lo lus teb for the currently qhib daim npav — the AI places it in the correct slot and marks it as a xib fwb-revealed lo lus teb (so the analytics distinguish tub ntxhais kawm-solved from xib fwb-revealed). Siv as a 'productive surrender' kev xaiv when a tub ntxhais kawm has been stuck for over a minute and frustration outweighs learning. The revealed daim npav still appears in the final sequence; only the analytics flag changes. cov lus qhia: in pairs/groups, siv reveal as a discussion prompt after the reveal — 'Why does qhov no event go HERE? What clues did we miss?' converts a stuck moment into a metacognition opportunity.",
    "quiz_item_mix_toggle": "Expand to teeb per-type lo lus nug counts for granular control over kev sim composition. Defaults: the base MCQ suav and reflection suav are teeb above; qhov no tshooj controls everything else (matching, true/false, luv-lo lus teb, application, etc.). Each lo lus nug type qhia its current suav tom ntej to a tus lej stepper (0-5 per type). Siv when: building targeted formative checks (e.g., '4 matching, 0 of everything else' for cov lus day), tab tom tsim standardized xyaum kev xeem with tshwj xeeb yam-type ratios, or accommodating IEP testing requirements qhov ntawd hais kom meej yam hom. Pib dua pob nias reverts to hom defaults. cov lus qhia: for Pre-Check probes, lean heavy on MCQ and 1-2 luv-lo lus teb; for Exit Tickets, 2-3 reflection yam beat 10 MCQ for revealing what tub ntxhais kawm actually understood.",
    "math_fluency_maze_panel": "Fluency Maze: a torchlit dungeon-crawler where each gate is locked by a math fact — daws teeb meem it to pass through. kev ua si wraps fluency drill in an exploration mechanic so the xyaum doesn't feel like worksheets. Designed for tier-2 math intervention (tub ntxhais kawm working on kev sib ntxiv/kev rho tawm/kev sib tshooj fluency to mastery) and for Math Recovery-hom programs where retrieval xyaum is the core treatment. Adaptive kev nyuaj: streaks of correct lo lus teb unlock harder facts; misses tso back to easier rooms. Find the golden key to unlock the maze exit and earn XP. cov lus qhia: 5-10 minute kev sib ntsib, 3-4 times a week beats one ntev kev sib ntsib for fluency development — the spaced retrieval matters ntau than total time on task.",
    "anchor_chart_view_panel": "The rendered EL-hom anchor chart — the artifact you would project on the smartboard or luam tawm as a wall poster. Built from the structure/yam the AI drafted in the sidebar, with hand-drawn-hom lub cim qhov ntawd anchor each tshooj visually. The chart is fully editable in kho hom (title, tshooj labels, bullet yam, rub-to-reorder, regenerate lub cim), and kev txhawb a Critique hom where tub ntxhais kawm post sticky-note hom annotations. cov lus qhia: in EL classrooms, project the chart and co-construct it WITH tub ntxhais kawm during the zaj lus qhia rather than presenting it as a finished artifact — co-construction builds investment and signals the chart belongs to the chav kawm.",
